Source: Canada Now [edited]
<http://www.ecanadanow.com/science/health/2007/01/01/rift-valley-fever-claims-more-lives/>

Kenya: Rift Valley fever Claims More Lives
-----------------------------------------------
Six people have died of the killer Rift Valley fever in Tana River
district, as the disease continues to takes its toll in parts of North
Eastern Kenya. Coast Provincial Veterinary Services Director Dr. George
Makalo on Fri 29 Dec 2006 said the deaths were revealed at a district
disaster management meeting at Hola in Tana River today [Mon 1 Jan 2007].
Makalo also said 125 goats, 28 camels and 14 sheep died from the fever in
Bangale and Madogo divisions, which neighbor Garissa, where the disease has
killed more than 10 people. Makalo said that, owing to the deaths of some
villagers, the whole district has been put under quarantine, while all the
slaughterhouses have been closed down.
A team of experts from Nairobi is in Tana River to survey and work out ways
of containing the disease.
